CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 17, 1956, pg. B14, reads: "Happy Pair - After their marriage at the home of the bride's mother, 2126 Wylie Ave., Mr. and Mrs. Lee Walls cued the reception by cutting the cake. The bride is the former Lucille Thomas, daughter of Mrs. Alberta Thomas. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Groom Lee Walls, and bride Lucille Thomas Walls wearing dress with ruched neckline, cutting three tiered wedding cake, in Thomas home, 2126 Wylie Avenue, Hill District
